{
  "id": "10047",
  "key": "GG-44",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Implement Hierarchical Relationship Structure in JSON Output",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use case:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "member of Team Gamma responsible for the JSON export functionality",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "I want to "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "implement the hierarchical relationship structure in the JSON output",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "so that "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "other teams can consume the exported data and maintain the parent-child links during the Jira data migration process",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance criteria:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the export operation is triggered,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the JSON output is generated,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the hierarchical relationships are included for epics, stories, and sub-tasks,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the JSON output must clearly represent the parent-child links and hierarchy for all relevant Jira issues."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Technical notes:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The hierarchical relationship structure in the JSON output should be organized to reflect the parent-child links between epics, stories, and sub-tasks. This includes creating a clear representation of how each level of issue is related to its parent and any children it may have. Each issue type should be clearly documented within the JSON schema, ensuring that Team EithanYsusEnemigos can easily replicate these relationships in Azure DevOps. Additionally, care should be taken to ensure that all related fields, transitions, and states are maintained within this hierarchical structure. This will facilitate a smooth and accurate migration process for all teams involved."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The JSON output should also include any necessary mapping references, such as old Jira IDs, to assist Team EithanYsusEnemigos in accurately replicating the items in Azure DevOps. The exported data should be well-structured and documented to allow for easy consumption by other teams while preserving the integrity of hierarchical relationships."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "It is crucial to validate the hierarchical data integrity within the exported JSON to ensure that all parent-child links are accurately represented. Furthermore, this functionality should be integrated into the Node JS backend's data retrieval process from Jira Cloud, ensuring that hierarchical relationships are logged during data fetch and maintained throughout processing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Finally, clear documentation should be provided to aid Team SinChambaTeam in incorporating Zephyr test data and relations with test artifacts independently while utilizing the hierarchical structure present in the JSON output."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
